I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve the API data, as this is the first step in the workflow.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_validator tool to validate the structure of the fetched API data, as this is the next logical step in the workflow.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_parser tool to parse the validated data into the required format, completing the three-step processing workflow.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I understand the task is complete, but since the system requires a tool call, I'll verify the final result by checking the output file:

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/output.json",
  "options": {"verify_only": true}
}
</tool_call>
